Physical description refers to the appearance or features of a given chemical compound including color, odor, state, taste and more in general

StringWithMarkup.String: Dichlorodifluoromethane appears as a colorless gas having a faint ethereal odor. Shipped as a liquid confined under its own vapor pressure. Contact with the unconfined liquid can cause frostbite. Both components are noncombustible. Can asphyxiate by the displacement of air. Exposure of the closed container to prolonged heat or fire can cause it to rupture violently and rocket.
COLOURLESS COMPRESSED LIQUEFIED GAS WITH CHARACTERISTIC ODOUR.
Colorless gas with an ether-like odor at extremely high concentrations.
Colorless gas with an ether-like odor at extremely high concentrations. [Note: Shipped as a liquefied compressed gas.]
